HEADWORD: Cadre
<hw>Ca"dre</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>cadre</ets>, It. <ets>quadro</ets> square, from L.
<ets>quadrum</ets>, fr. <ets>quatuor</ets> four.]</ety>
<fld>(Mil.)</fld> <def>The framework or skeleton upon which a regiment
is to be formed; the officers of a regiment forming the staff.</def>
<altsp>[Written also <asp>cader</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Caducary</ent>⟦br⟧
